In its latest Technology, Media & Telecommunications (TMT) Predictions report released on Monday, Deloitte said companies would further accelerate use of cloud-based artificial intelligence software and services, while fifth-generation (5G) wireless networks were expected to arrive in scale, providing faster connections and opening revenue opportunities for telecommunication companies. “Smart speakers are continuing to fly off shelves, selling 164 million units at an average selling price of $43 (R600) per unit,” it said. 